<h2 class="mt-3">Get Master Funding Source</h2>
<p>Now that we have the location of the master account, we can find the funding source on the account and make it the
	source of the transfer. Again, this is something that would be card coded into an application.</p>
<form action="/funding-sources/send/get-master-funding-source" method="POST" class="mt-3">
	<div class="form-group" onload="setValues()">

		<input type="hidden" class="form-control" id="key" name="key">
		<input type="hidden" class="form-control" id="secret" name="secret">
		<input type="hidden" class="form-control" id="masterAccount" name="masterAccount">
		<div class="col mx-4">
			<p class="font-weight-bold text-center">HTTP request</p>
			<code>GET https://api.dwolla.com/accounts/{id}/funding-sources?removed=false</code>
			<p class="font-weight-bold text-center mt-3">Example Body Request</p>
		</div>
		<button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary btn-block mt-3">Get Master Funding Source</button>
	</div>
</form>
<script>
	function setValues() {
		document.querySelector('#key').value = localStorage.getItem('key');
		document.querySelector('#secret').value = localStorage.getItem('secret');
		document.querySelector('#masterAccount').value = localStorage.getItem('masterAccount');
	}
	window.onload = setValues;
</script>